\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}3/4 cup {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/panko/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 panko bread crumbs}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons butter, melted\
{\listtext	\'95	}Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 For the mac 'n' cheese: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil in a large pot. Salt generously, and then add the pasta and cook to box instructions, usually 6 to 7 minutes. Drain.\
In another large pot, melt the butter over medium-high heat. Whisk in the flour and continue whisking until it deepens in color and releases a light toasted aroma, about 1 minute.\
Whisk in the Thai red {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/curry-paste/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 curry paste}}, and when fully combined, pour in the milk and cream (or all milk, if using). Bring to a boil, whisking constantly, and then turn down to a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/simmer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simmer}}. Simmer until the mixture thickens, whisking occasionally, about 5 minutes.\
Off heat, whisk in the cheeses and stir until melted. Add the pasta and toss to combine.\
Turn your broiler on.\
For the crumb topping: Toss the panko with the melted {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/butter/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 butter}} and season with salt and pepper.\
To assemble: Pour the mac 'n' cheese into a broiler-safe {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/casserole/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 casserole dish}}, sprinkle with the bread crumb mixture, and broil until browned, about 1 minute.\
